# Divido Chatbot — Flutter Integration Guide

Provided by The Osiris Labs.

## What You Receive
- `divido_chat_widget.dart` — self-contained chat widget
- This guide

---

## Step 1 — Add the File
Copy `divido_chat_widget.dart` into your Flutter project:
```
lib/widgets/divido_chat_widget.dart
```

---

## Step 2 — Add Dependencies
Open `pubspec.yaml` and add under `dependencies`:
```yaml
dependencies:
  http: ^1.2.0
  flutter_markdown: ^0.7.3
  shared_preferences: ^2.5.3
```

Then run:
```bash
flutter pub get
```

---

## Step 3 — Place the Widget
Import and add the widget inside a `Stack` on any screen
where you want the chat button to appear (recommended: home screen):
```dart
import 'package:your_app/widgets/divido_chat_widget.dart';

Scaffold(
  body: Stack(
    children: [
      YourExistingScreenContent(),
      DividoChatWidget(
        apiBaseUrl: 'https://yourdomain.com',
      ),
    ],
  ),
)
```

---

## Step 4 — Set the API URL
Replace `https://yourdomain.com` with the production URL
provided by The Osiris Labs after server deployment.

**Do not use the URL until it is confirmed by The Osiris Labs —
the server must be live and tested first.**

---

## What the Widget Does
- Floating chat button (bottom-right, above nav bar)
- Slides up into a full chat panel
- Supports English and Arabic
- Streaming responses from the Divido AI backend
- Handles its own state — no additional setup needed

